				                <div>&lt;div style=&quot;background-color: #FFF; padding-left: 10px;&quot;&gt;Hello swolock,<br />
<br />
No problem at all, glad to help! If you've already &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/website/wordpress/prevent-unauthorized-wp-admin-wp-login-php-attempts&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;setup a secondary WordPress password&lt;/a&gt; for your site, it's probably not necessary to also &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/website/wordpress/lock-down-wordpress-admin-login-with-htaccess&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;restrict access to WordPress admin by IP address&lt;/a&gt;.<br />
<br />
Most bots won't attempt to guess your secondary WordPress password, as they're expecting to be seeing a WordPress login form, and not a &lt;strong&gt;.htaccess&lt;/strong&gt; password prompt pop-up. If you're restricting access by IP and just wanted an additional level of security on top of that it won't hurt to have both, but again it's probably not needed since either way you're greatly minimizing the potential of a malicious user guessing your valid WordPress admin credentials.<br />
<br />
- Jacob&lt;/div&gt;</div>
